# Deobfuscated Code

Here's the fully deobfuscated and readable version:

```javascript
var TAU = 6.283;        // 2π
var PHI = 1.618;        // Golden ratio
var SQRT_HALF = 0.707;  // √(1/2)

// Physics simulation parameters
var config = {
  attraction: 4000,        // Repulsive force strength between all node pairs
  frictionCoeff: 0.004,    // Spring friction/stiffness coefficient
  amplification: 0.92,     // Velocity damping factor per frame
  dispersal: 0.0003,       // Centering/gravity force strength
  streamMax: 40,           // Maximum number of particles
  streamDecay: 0.04,       // Particle velocity decay rate
  theta: 0.06              // Camera smoothing interpolation factor
};

// === NODE DEFINITIONS ===
var nodes = [
  { id: 'hub',      label: 'Kieleth', r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'alpha',    label: 'Alpha',   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'beta',     label: 'Beta',    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'gamma',    label: 'Gamma',   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'delta',    label: 'Delta',   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'epsilon',  label: 'Epsilon', r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// === EDGE/SPRING DEFINITIONS ===
// Each edge connects two nodes with a rest length and spring constant
var edges = [
  { a: 'hub', b: 'alpha',   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
  { a: 'hub', b: 'beta',    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
  { a: 'hub', b: 'gamma',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: 'hub', b: 'delta',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: 'hub', b: 'epsilon', rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
  { a: 'alpha', b: 'beta',    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
  { a: 'gamma', b: 'delta',   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
  { a: 'alpha', b: 'epsilon', rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// === CAMERA STATE ===
var camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// === PARTICLE SYSTEM ===
var particles = [];
var frameCount = 0;

// Helper: find a node by its ID
function findNode(id) {
  for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
  }
  return null;
}

// === MAIN PHYSICS STEP ===
function physicsStep() {
  // 1) REPULSIVE FORCES between all node pairs (Coulomb-like)
  for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
      var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
      var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
      var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
      var force = config.attraction / (dist * dist);
      var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
      var fy = (dy / dist) * force;

      nodes[i].vx += fx;
      nodes[i].vy += fy;
      nodes[j].vx -= fx;
      nodes[j].vy -= fy;
    }
  }

  // 2) SPRING FORCES along edges (Hooke's law)
  for (var e = 0; e < edges.length; e++) {
    var nodeA = findNode(edges[e].a);
    var nodeB = findNode(edges[e].b);
    if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;

    var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
    var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
    var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
    var displacement = dist - edges[e].rest;
    var force = (edges[e].k || config.frictionCoeff) * displacement;

    nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
    nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
    nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
    nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
  }

  // 3) VELOCITY DAMPING + CENTERING GRAVITY + POSITION UPDATE
  for (var n = 0; n < nodes.length; n++) {
    // Centering force pulls nodes toward (400, 300)
    nodes[n].vx += (400 - nodes[n].x) * config.dispersal;
    nodes[n].vy += (300 - nodes[n].y) * config.dispersal;

    // Damping (multiply velocity by amplification factor < 1)
    nodes[n].vx *= config.amplification;
    nodes[n].vy *= config.amplification;

    // Euler integration: update positions
    nodes[n].x += nodes[n].vx;
    nodes[n].y += nodes[n].vy;
  }
}

// === PARTICLE SPAWNER ===
function spawnParticle() {
  if (particles.length >= config.streamMax) return;

  // Pick a random node as spawn point
  var sourceNode = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;

  particles.push({
    x: sourceNode.x,
    y: sourceNode.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + (Math.random() * PHI) * SQRT_HALF
  });
}

// === PARTICLE UPDATE ===
function updateParticles() {
  for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    var p = particles[i];

    // Apply velocity decay
    p.vx *= (1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125);
    p.vy *= (1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125);

    // Move particle
    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;

    // Age and remove expired particles
    p.age++;
    if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
      particles.splice(i, 1);
    }
  }
}

// === CAMERA SMOOTHING ===
function updateCamera() {
  camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.theta;
  camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.theta;
  camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.theta;
}

// === MAIN LOOP ===
function tick() {
  physicsStep();
  updateParticles();
  updateCamera();

  // Spawn a new particle every 3rd frame
  if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
  frameCount++;
}

setInterval(tick, 16); // ~60 FPS
```

---

## What It Does

This is the **physics engine** for a **force-directed graph visualization**. Here's what each system does:

### 1. Force-Directed Graph Layout
A classic force-directed layout with three forces combined each frame:

| Force | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| **Repulsion** (Coulomb's law) | All node pairs repel each other with force `attraction / dist²`, preventing overlap |
| **Springs** (Hooke's law) | Connected nodes are pulled toward each other with `force = k × (distance - restLength)` |
| **Centering gravity** | A weak force (`dispersal`) pulls all nodes toward the canvas center (400, 300) |

After forces are applied, velocities are **damped** by the `amplification` factor (0.92) each frame — this is actually a **damping/friction** coefficient, not amplification. It bleeds off 8% of kinetic energy per frame so the graph settles to equilibrium.

### 2. Particle System
Decorative particles spawn from random nodes, drift outward at random angles, slow down via `streamDecay`, and die after 800–2000 frames. Capped at 40 particles, spawning every 3rd frame.

### 3. Smooth Camera
The camera position/zoom smoothly interpolates toward a target using `theta` (0.06) as the lerp factor — a classic exponential ease-out.

### 4. The Graph Structure
A **hub-and-spoke** graph with "Kieleth" as the central hub (largest node, r=26) connected to 5 satellite nodes (Alpha, Beta, Gamma, Delta, Epsilon), plus three cross-links between satellites.

### Note on the Blog Post's Misleading Descriptions

The blog post descriptions are **intentionally misleading/inverted**:

- **"attraction"** → Actually controls **repulsion** (inverse-square repulsive force)
- **"amplification"** → Actually **damping** (multiplying velocity by 0.92 removes energy each frame)
- **"frictionCoeff"** → Actually the **spring constant** for edges
- **"dispersal"** → Actually a **centering/gravity** force pulling nodes *toward* center, not pushing them to edges
- **"inertiaCore"/"inertiaNode"** → Don't appear in the code at all
